1. Stochastic CCP1, 5000 iterations

1.1 Distribution of beta and delta

ggplot(c1est, aes(x = beta)) + geom_density()

ggplot(c1est, aes(x = delta)) + geom_density()

1.2 Average rhat across the sample

Rstan documentation says they recommend “only using the sample if R-hat is less than 1.05”. We pass this rule in CCP1 (barely).

#for beta
rhat(hier_time, pars = "mubeta")
## [1] 1.016729
#for delta
rhat(hier_time, pars = "mudelta_phi")
## [1] 1.002674
#for theta (the error?)
rhat(hier_time, pars = "mutheta")
## [1] 1.18554
##add for a few individuals

1.3 Correlation between beta and delta

Two things that surprised me about the stochastic results is there are now many deltas of exactly 1, and the correlations between beta and delta are now negative.

#beta and delta (annual discount factor) correlation
cor(c1est$beta,c1est$delta)
## [1] -0.0960174
plot(c1est$beta,c1est$delta)
